.TH git-sqlite-smudge 1 "January 2026" "git-sqlite-filter" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-sqlite-smudge \- Git smudge filter for SQLite databases
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-sqlite-smudge
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIFILE\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git-sqlite-smudge
is a Git filter that rebuilds a binary SQLite database from a deterministic SQL dump on stdin.
It automatically discovers and registers missing custom collation functions during the restoration process.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-schema \fIFILE\fR
Apply a base schema from \fIFILE\fR before processing the input dump.
.TP
.B \-\-debug
Output diagnostic information and the processed SQL stream to stderr.
.SH SEE ALSO
git-sqlite-clean(1)
